n, k = map(int, input().split())
    arr = list(map(int, input().split()))
    arr.sort()
    ans = 0
    for i in range(n):
        curr_sum = arr[i]
        for j in range(i+1, n):
            curr_sum += arr[j]
            if curr_sum > k:
                break
            ans += 1
    print(ans)

code()

n, k = map(int, input().split())
    prices = list(map(int, input().split()))
    prices.sort()
    count = 0
    for i in prices:
        if k - i >= 0:
            count += 1
            k -= i
        else:
            break
    print(count)
